  "prompt": "How do I communicate with my wife so she stops complaining and sending me no good vibes?",
  "response": "Effective communication is key to a healthy relationship. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Listen actively\n- Pay full attention when she's speaking\n- Don't interrupt\n- Show you understand her feelings\n\n2. Use \"I\" statements\n- Express your feelings without blaming\n- Example: \"I feel frustrated when...\" instead of \"You always...\"\n\n3. Show empathy\n- Try to understand her perspective\n- Validate her feelings\n- Ask open-ended questions\n\n4. Choose the right time to talk\n- Find a calm moment\n- Avoid discussing issues when tired or stressed\n\n5. Be open and honest\n- Share your own feelings\n- Discuss problems constructively\n- Work together to find solutions\n\n6. Seek to understand the root cause\n- Her complaints might stem from deeper issues\n- Ask what's really bothering her\n\n7. Practice mutual respect\n- Treat each other with kindness\n- Avoid criticism and defensiveness\n\n8. Consider counseling\n- If communication remains difficult\n- A professional can help improve communication skills\n\nRemember, strong relationships require ongoing effort and understanding from both partners.",
